---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Why The Learning Map of India exists.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">About the project</p>
      <h1>Why a map, and why education?</h1>
      <p>
        India publishes an enormous amount of education data — school
        infrastructure, learning outcomes, enrollment, spending — but most of
        it lives in dense spreadsheets and PDF reports that few people ever
        open.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Learning Map of India takes that data and gives it a shape: one
        map, one topic, one clear takeaway at a time. The goal is a resource
        that a class 10 student researching a school project, a journalist on
        deadline, and a policy researcher can all use the same afternoon.
      </p>
      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <p>
        Every map on this site traces back to a named, dated public source —
        no modeled estimates presented as fact, no numbers without a
        citation. As the atlas grows, this page will grow with it: notes on
        corrections, methodology changes, and the occasional map that didn't
        work out.
      </p>
      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Have a dataset worth mapping, or spotted an error? This project is
        built in the open — reach out on [add your contact or social handle
        here].
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .section p {
    margin-bottom: 1.2em;
  }
</style>
